# OpenAPI & SDK

## Swagger JSDoc on every public route

Every file under `app/src/app/api/v1/**` that exports an HTTP handler must include a `@swagger` JSDoc block above the imports describing the route, parameters, and response schema. This is consumed by `next-swagger-doc` and feeds `public/openapi-spec.json`.

Template:

```ts
/**
 * @swagger
 * /api/v1/widget/{widget}:
 *   get:
 *     operationId: getWidget
 *     summary: Get a widget by id
 *     tags: [widget]
 *     parameters:
 *       - in: path
 *         name: widget
 *         required: true
 *         schema: { type: string, format: uuid }
 *     responses:
 *       200:
 *         description: Success
 *         content:
 *           application/json:
 *             schema:
 *               type: object
 *               properties:
 *                 data: { $ref: '#/components/schemas/Widget' }
 *       404: { description: Not found }
 */
```

Don't invent new tags — reuse the existing tag set (`inventory`, `city`, `organization`, `user`, `auth`, `hiap`, `ccra`, `chat`, `cron`, `policy-signal`, `project`, …).

## Lint the spec on every API change

Before pushing changes to anything under `src/app/api/` or `src/api/`:

```bash
cd app
npm run openapi:lint
```

This runs Spectral against `public/openapi-spec.json`. CI runs it too — fix locally to avoid round-trips.

## SDK generator workflow

`.github/workflows/sdk-generator.yml` triggers on **any push** that touches `app/src/api/**`. It builds the app, lints the OpenAPI spec, and uploads the spec as a CI artifact.

When you change the API surface, expect this workflow to run. If it fails, the spec is broken — fix the JSDoc.

## Versioning

The current public surface is `/api/v1/`. **Do not** introduce `/api/v2/` without core-team sign-off — we'd rather extend v1 carefully (additive fields, optional params, deprecation headers) than fork.

`/api/v0/` exists for k8s probes (`liveness`, `health`) and a few legacy proxies. Don't add new public routes there.
